ARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uhippolyte.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 393<br> <font color=#993300>(7/17/01 4:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=237.topic&index=40>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/hipprpg.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: a joining?</span><hr size=1> As soon as Hippolyte slowely stood up, as if called priestess of the tribe came out of the woodwork. Four priestesses were carrying elemental symbols: a basket of grain for Earth, a carved crystal lotus bowl with salt water and floating water lilies for Water, a crystal torch for Fire, and a bell jar of butterflies for Air. Four other priestesses walked to altars located on the perimeter of the hall, at the four compass points.<br>
<br>
Attendants walk around the couple and altar once counterclockwise, with element-bearers scattering grain, sprinkling water, waving incense, and lighting candles to invoke the elements. Last person scattered the rosepetals. As each element-bearer reached the appropriate elemental altar, she stopped. Finally, two priestesses split the lovers and walked them up to the Queen's either side.<br>
<br>
As all stood quietly, the priestess at the far four points envoked the spirits.<br>
The first held her bowl up high and spoke, "Spirits of Earth, we welcome you to this circle. In the name of this grain, we ask you to bless this circle and all within."<br>
Then the second one lighted her torch and spoke, "Spirits of Fire, we welcome you to this circle. In the name of these flames which blaze on your altar, we ask you to purify this circle and all within."<br>
The third smiled and then released the butterflies, "Spirits of Air, we welcome you to this circle. In the name of these spirits of Air, we ask you to release fear from this circle and all within."<br>
Then the final fourth offered up the salt she carried, "Spirits of Water, we welcome you to this circle. Here is the salt water which represents the living womb. We ask you to protect this circle and all within."<br>
Hippolyte gazed at the two lovers and then turned her back to them all...facing Hera's altar again. "I call to mind the Queen of the Gods, who watches over this world, by her own power with her three Aspects Preserves it, and, having destroyed it, she then plays.<br>
The first priestess called out, "You are Earth, Creatrix of the World."<br>
Then the second, "You are Water, and in the form of Diana You preserve the World."<br>
The third, "You are Fire, and in the form of Pele You destroy the World."<br>
Then finally again the fourth, "You are Air; you are the inspiration of the World."<br>
Hippolyte gazed into the mirror, "Great Queen of the Gods, be welcome here. You have bound these hearts together; come into this circle where lovers await your blessing!<br>
<br>
